<div id="review_2856958305" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2856958305" />
    <a title="Adina" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/22189348-adina"><img alt="Adina" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1531917330p2/22189348.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2856958305?book_show_action=true">Apr 08, 2020</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Adina" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Adina" href="/user/show/22189348-adina">Adina</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/22189348-adina?shelf=urban-fantasy-pr">urban-fantasy-pr</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2856958305" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer2300436508249007951">I wanted to take a break from the grim and violence of the Booker International Prize and I thought a bit of Urban Fantasy will do me good. <br/><br/>Grave Peril was exactly what I needed. Pure action, fun, no need to think and no heaviness in my chest. Although people say this is better than the first two, I enjoyed the previous efforts more. The reason might be my not so positive mood in the past weeks. This social distancing business is getting too much too bear but we must soldier on so we can beat th</span>
  <span id="freeText2300436508249007951" style="display:none">I wanted to take a break from the grim and violence of the Booker International Prize and I thought a bit of Urban Fantasy will do me good. <br /><br />Grave Peril was exactly what I needed. Pure action, fun, no need to think and no heaviness in my chest. Although people say this is better than the first two, I enjoyed the previous efforts more. The reason might be my not so positive mood in the past weeks. This social distancing business is getting too much too bear but we must soldier on so we can beat the invisible monster which is much more dangerous than the ones in this book (i.e. vampires and ghosts). <br /><br />I enjoyed Michael, the new character, a magical Christian knight and the fact that we get a glimpse of Dresden's past. What I did not like, was that the plot was overcrowded, too many things were happening and it made me dizzy. <br /></span>
  <a data-text-id="2300436508249007951" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


