        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer967720300" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer8235644960984051028">There seems to be a common idea amongst fans and new arrivals alike to this series, that this, the third book in the series, is where it starts to get good. I’ve read the series and started again while I’m waiting for the next volume- I think the first two are great too. This one just ramps up the action and its consequences. And this might be the one where Harry Dresden starts to slip-by his own standards- taking actions and committing deeds that in an ideal world he would not have chosen to do</span>
  <span id="freeText8235644960984051028" style="display:none">There seems to be a common idea amongst fans and new arrivals alike to this series, that this, the third book in the series, is where it starts to get good. I’ve read the series and started again while I’m waiting for the next volume- I think the first two are great too. This one just ramps up the action and its consequences. And this might be the one where Harry Dresden starts to slip-by his own standards- taking actions and committing deeds that in an ideal world he would not have chosen to do. Harry is the ultimate underdog in a way. He’s always up against impossible odds, often achieving impossible feats with very little in the way of resources. This book is a game changer in terms of the overall story arc and in terms of characters new to the scene as well as character development of established players. Another great read.</span>
